author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Lalu Prasad Yadav's daughter, Rohini Acharya, has accused her brother Tejashwi Yadav and aides Sanjay Yadav and Rameez Nemat of forcing her out of the family and silencing her after the RJD's election defeat. Acharya claimed she was abused and physically harmed for questioning the party's performance. This internal turmoil highlights significant cracks within the prominent political family.
title: Who is Rameez Nemat? The man behind Rohini Acharya’s exit from RJD

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: High fasting blood sugar in the morning can be due to the dawn phenomenon, a natural hormone surge, or the less common Somogyi effect, a rebound from low overnight glucose. Experts like Dr. Joseph Tejero emphasize that stress, poor sleep, late meals, and medication timing also contribute, requiring a holistic management approach.
title: Why your morning blood sugar is high: Key risk factors and how to manage it

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Thousands protested drug violence and President Sheinbaum's security policies in Mexico City, with many carrying the 'One Piece' pirate flag. The demonstration, organized by 'Generation Z,' saw clashes with police outside the National Palace. Protesters honored assassinated Mayor Carlos Manzo, though his widow distanced herself from the event.
title: Tear gas, chaos, and straw hats: Gen Z protests erupt in Mexico — watch

author: ZARAFSHAN SHIRAZ
description: Feeling overwhelmed? Psychic counsellor suggests five simple daily meditation habits. These brief practices help calm your mind and return you to yourself faster. They are designed to be easy to incorporate into your routine. Try them for two weeks and notice the difference in your emotional strength. This is about building resilience.
title: 5 meditation habits that build emotional strength in just 2 weeks

author: TNN
description: An RSS worker died by suicide in Thiruvananthapuram after allegedly being denied a BJP ticket for local body elections. The deceased, Anand Thampi, named several BJP and RSS leaders in his suicide note, accusing them of involvement in a 'soil mafia' and citing harassment. His death follows a pattern of suicides linked to RSS-BJP circles in recent months.
title: Denied BJP ticket, RSS man dies by suicide in Thiruvananthapuram

author: IP SINGH
description: A 48-year-old woman, Sarabjeet Kaur, who accompanied a Sikh Jatha to Pakistan, has reportedly embraced Islam and married a Pakistani citizen, Naseer Hussain, of her own free will. She appeared before a magistrate in Sheikhupura, adopting the name Noor and stating she wished to live with her husband.  Her family in India was reportedly unaware of her decision until recently.
title: 'Missing' Punjab woman Sarabjeet Kaur, embraces Islam, marries Pakistani man

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Nine-millimeter caliber cartridges, prohibited for civilian use, were recovered from the Red Fort blast site, adding a new dimension to the investigation. Police are probing the source of the ammunition and potential links to terror networks. The National Medical Commission has also cancelled the registration of four doctors from Jammu and Kashmir in connection with the case.
title: 'Possessed by armed forces': 9mm cartridges recovered at Delhi car blast site

author: DWAIPAYAN DATTA
description: Sanju Samson's arrival at CSK bolsters their top-order batting, potentially signaling MS Dhoni's final season. With Ruturaj Gaikwad captaining, Samson joins the leadership group and may even don the gloves, allowing Dhoni to feature as an impact sub. This setup could facilitate Dhoni's farewell at Chepauk, fulfilling a promise to fans.
title: Sanju Samson’s inclusion could be catalyst for MS Dhoni’s last dance for CSK

author: TNN
description: A stone quarry caved in Sonbhadra, Uttar Pradesh, on Saturday afternoon, resulting in one worker's death and at least eight feared trapped. Rescue operations are underway by NDRF and SDRF teams, hindered by darkness and the quarry's significant depth. Officials are investigating the incident, with quarry owners reportedly fleeing.
title: Stone quarry collapse in UP's Sonbhadra: 1 dead, 8 feared trapped

author: KUSHAGRA DIXIT
title: Delhi air quality stays very poor; severe pollution expected by Monday

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Taylor Swift's new song, 'The Fate of Ophelia,' is fueling fan theories linking it to her breakup with Joe Alwyn.  Swifties interpret lyrics about rescue and rebirth as a nod to her current relationship, contrasting it with her past. The track is seen as Swift reclaiming her narrative, transforming heartbreak into art.
title: ‘The Fate of Ophelia’ sparks theories: Taylor Swift revisits her Joe Alwyn breakup

author: TOI
title: Kids with sight, hearing disabilities decode bird calls in U’khand avian census

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru faces backlash for retaining fast-bowler Yash Dayal for IPL 2026. Dayal faces serious criminal allegations in Ghaziabad and Jaipur. These include sexual and financial exploitation, and rape charges. He is banned from Uttar Pradesh's local league. RCB's decision to keep him on a Rs 5 crore contract has angered fans.
title: Controversial! 'Kohli, Dayal in same poster, what a shame': RCB slammed

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Indian cricket captain Shubman Gill has been ruled out of the ongoing Test match against South Africa due to a neck injury sustained on Day 2. The incident occurred during a shot, leading to immediate discomfort and subsequent hospital examination. Gill will remain under observation by the BCCI medical team.
title: IND vs SA: Gill ruled out of Eden Gardens Test; BCCI shares latest update

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: Kayla Nicole faces renewed online backlash over decade-old offensive tweets. Her subsequent apology has ignited a debate, with accusations of using AI to craft her statement. Critics question the sincerity of her remorse, while others argue the focus should be on her growth and acknowledging past harm, not AI detection.
title: Kayla Nicole accused of using AI for apology as fans analyse her statement

author: TNN
description: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath likened the bond between Uttar Pradesh and Bihar to that of Lord Ram and Sita, celebrating the NDA's landslide victory in Bihar. He inaugurated and laid foundations for 432 projects worth Rs 548 crore in Sonbhadra, emphasizing development and good governance for tribal communities.
title: Bihar-UP relationship like Ram-Sita, ‘unbreakable and strong’, says UP CM Yogi

author: TNN
title: CDS lashes out at defence companies: 'Show a bit of patriotism'

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: Doctor Umar Un Nabi, central to a Delhi terror plot, hid for 10 days in Nuh before the Red Fort metro station bombing. Investigators are tracking a hawala network used by the radicalized doctors' module. Raids were conducted across Nuh and Faridabad, including searches at Al-Falah University.
title: Dr Umar’s escape: How Delhi ‘bomber’ fled Al-Falah University after Dr Muzammil’s arrest

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Teenage sensation Vaibhav Suryavanshi's grounded approach is highlighted in a recent BCCI video, showcasing a post-match chat with his father. Despite a record-breaking performance, his father still offered technical advice, emphasizing a balanced perspective on his game. Suryavanshi's humility and focus on team contribution shine through, even amidst immense public expectations.
title: ‘Even if I scored 200’: Suryavanshi reveals father's tough love

author: TNN
description: Police in Kodagu have launched an investigation after three men were apprehended transporting a woman's body. The deceased, identified as Nanki Devi from Haryana, was found in a car during a routine check. Her husband and two others were detained. They claimed to be taking her to a hospital. Police suspect they intended to dispose of the body.
title: Karnataka shocker: Man held while transporting wife’s body with 2 others

author: VISHAL RAJEMAHADIK
description: A 13-year-old girl tragically died after being subjected to 100 sit-ups with her schoolbag on her back for being ten minutes late. The Vasai student developed severe back pain following the punishment and her health rapidly declined. While police have registered an accidental death report, the family holds the school and teacher accountable. Investigations are ongoing pending the post-mortem report.
title: Maharashtra shocker: Made to do 100 sit-ups with bag for being late, girl dies

author: ABHAY
description: Fresh CCTV footage reveals car bomber Umar Un Nabi using two phones and visiting a tea shop before the Red Fort blast.  Investigators tracked his movements across Delhi, including visits to Mayur Vihar and Connaught Place, before he reached the Red Fort parking lot.  The blast's impact was felt even at the metro station.
title: Delhi car blast: How video grabs from 50 CCTVs helped track Umar’s movements

author: BHARTI JAIN
description: Dr. Umer Un Nabi, the alleged bomber behind the Red Fort blast, operated a home laboratory in Faridabad to test explosives and build Improvised Explosive Devices (IEDs). He received bomb-making instructions and radicalization videos from Pakistani handlers via Telegram. Investigations revealed large caches of explosives at separate locations.
title: Delhi blast: Bomber had lab at home to test explosives; used techniques shared by Pak handlers

author: AMIT ANAND CHOUDHARY
description: The Supreme Court is set to hear a plea to lift a seven-year-old stay on a CBI probe into tiger poaching in Corbett Tiger Reserve. The probe had suggested forest officials' connivance with poachers. The CBI itself has sought vacation of the stay, citing preliminary findings of irregularities and cover-ups. An environmentalist argues the prolonged stay hinders dismantling poaching networks.
title: Ignoring own orders, Supreme Court has kept case in limbo since 2018

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: New research indicates Ozempic and Mounjaro offer significant cardiovascular benefits beyond weight loss and blood sugar control. A real-world study found these medications substantially reduced the risk of strokes and heart attacks in type 2 diabetes patients. These findings suggest a potential turning point in diabetes care, highlighting the drugs' protective effects on the heart.
title: Ozempic, Mounjaro cut stroke & heart attack risk in Diabetes

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
title: Delhi car blast: Cops suspect volatile TATP, ammonium nitrate behind explosion; bomb may not need detonator

author: BHARTI JAIN
title: Peaceful polls to boost SIR in other states/UTs: CEC hails final electoral roll of Bihar

author: SANJAY SHARMA
description: A hidden US career path is offering Gen Z the chance to earn over $300K annually without a college degree. Aviation maintenance technicians are in short supply, with 83% expected to retire globally in the next decade, creating thousands of opportunities. Short-term training programmes, including FAA certification, enable young workers to enter the field quickly. Airports nationwide and other skilled trades face labour shortages, driving high demand and lucrative compensation for qualified candidates.
title: Gen Z can earn $300K+ in a fast-rising US job with no degree: How can you get in?

author: NIRUPA VATYAM
description: Stricter US visa rules are forcing Telugu NRIs to scale down or postpone their Indian weddings. Many are opting for intimate ceremonies in the US, prioritizing visa security over traditional grand celebrations back home. Couples on H1B and F1 visas are seeking immigration advice, with some postponing nuptials due to visa uncertainties.
title: Trump-era visa jitters kill big fat Indian wedding dream for Telugus in US

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Alphabet's YouTube TV and Disney have reached a new carriage agreement, ending a two-week blackout of ABC and ESPN. The deal restores Disney's full channel lineup to the streaming platform and expands their partnership, including ESPN's direct-to-consumer service for subscribers at no extra cost.
title: Disney-YouTube blackout ends: Execs 'pleased' with deal; YouTube apologizes to viewers

author: MOHAMMAD ASIF
description: A 62-year-old retired headmaster, Nirmal Dutta, died after being stung by an estimated 890 bees near Durgapur's Major Park. He was attacked while stopping to help his son, who was initially stung. Despite rescue by police and hospital treatment, Dutta succumbed to his injuries on Friday.
title: 62-year-old man dies after being stung 890 times by bees; son escapes with injuries

author: DEVANSHI MEHTA
description: A devastating blast near Red Fort has left a deep psychological scar, impacting survivors, families, and first responders. Experts highlight the isolation of victims and the amplified trauma from graphic online visuals, especially for children. The incident triggers classic trauma responses, making everyday spaces feel threatening and demanding long-term mental health support.
title: Shocked & scared for life: Blasts take a toll on mental health too

author: MADAN KUMAR
description: The NDA's strong Bihar election win positions them to claim all Rajya Sabha seats from the state in upcoming biennial polls. This will significantly reduce the RJD's representation in the Upper House, as opposition parties lack the necessary MLA numbers to secure seats in 2026 and 2028. The NDA is set to bolster its numbers in the Rajya Sabha.
title: Bihar election result: RJD’s numbers in Rajya Sabha to shrink sharply after poll debacle

author: MADAN KUMAR
title: Bihar poll: Day after win, NDA mins throng Nitish's home; govt formation talks begin

author: JAI NARAIN PANDEY
title: Bihar poll: Nitish led from front; RJD stayed in illusion about its strength, says Chirag

author: TNN
title: ED nabs builder in PMAY scam: Judge holds 3am court to remand accused; allottees cheated

author: MANOJ CHAURASIA AND JAI NARAIN PANDEY
description: Rohini Acharya, daughter of Lalu Prasad, declared she has "no family left" after an electoral setback for the RJD. She accused Tejashwi Yadav's advisors, Sanjay Yadav and Rameez, of expelling her and blamed them for the party's poor performance. This public rift highlights deep internal party tensions and questions about leadership influence.
title: Row after rout: Rohini quits politics; JD(U) taunts Lalu, says 'must not act like Dhritarashtra'
